<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-041-056 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 336 703</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 1 1991 v5 n33 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New board eliminates the need for translation from RGB to CMYK.andO;(red-green-blue vs. cyan-magenta-yellow-black color display, CYMAKTechnologies' CYMAK Board, Press Simulator)(brief article)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   CYMAK Technologies Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   CYMAK Technologies CYMAK Board (Graphics board) (Productintroduction)CYMAK Technologies Press Simulator (Graphics board) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionColor SeparationGraphics boards/cardsData conversion.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Carolyn SaidandM;San Jose, Calif.andP;  -- Monitors display in RGB (red, green, blue).andP;  Pressesprint in CMYK (cyan, magenta, yellow, black).andP;  Therein lies the source ofmany a problem in getting accurate color output.andM;CYMAK Technologies this week will introduce a board set that lets computersmaintain the CMYK color model in video RAM.andP;  Although users can currentlywork on screen in CMYK modes in programs such as Adobe Photoshop 2.0, theboards will offer significant performance advantages, as well as eliminatethe need for translation between RGB and CMYK, thus reducing the potentialfor errors, CYMAK said.andM;andgt;CYMAK Board.andP;  A four-channel, 32-bit CMYK video display frame buffer, theCYMAK NuBus board contains dedicated CMYK-to-RGB conversion hardware.andP;  Itoffers 4 Mbytes of video RAM and built-in pan and zoom functions.andP;  The boardalso will be able to run in RGB mode, acting as a standard QuickDrawaccelerator, CYMAK said.andM;Users will benefit from the board's CMYK aspects only when using softwareoptimized for it.andP;  CYMAK said it is talking to companies about tailoringprograms to take advantage of the board, including Adobe Systems Inc. ofMountain View, Calif., for Photoshop 2.0.andM;andgt;Press Simulator board.andP;  This optional add-on board works with the CYMAKBoard to provide fast, continuous adjustment of displayed images to bettermatch printed results, the company said.andP;  It will include calibrationsoftware to customize the monitor's display of a printed image.andM;Using test patches printed on their press, users run calibration routines togenerate color-correction data.andM;Macintosh developer kits for both boards will be available in the fourthquarter.andP;  The company estimated that the CYMAK Board would reach end usersfor about $5,000, and the Press Simulator board would be about $3,500.andM;CYMAK Technologies is at 950 N. Rengstorff, Suite D, Mountain View, Calif.andO;94043.andP;  Phone (415) 968-9336; fax (415) 968-8930.andO;</TEXT></DOC>